If the capacity plan optimization engine exceeds its one-hour-per-job-profile time limit, we return plan data that isnâ€™t fully optimized. We call this data baseline capacity plan data.

Workforce Engagement is available in Lightning Experience and requires Enterprise, Performance, or Unlimited Editions.

During capacity plan creation, an optimization engine runs multiple iterations to find the best number of agents per hour for the requested input, satisfying service level agreement targets. This process has a one-hour time limit per job profile.

In some situations, the iterations exceed this limit, preventing completion of the optimization process for that profile. We return the best possible solution found until this point, called a baseline capacity plan.
title: Understanding Capacity Planning in Service Cloud
